No household with small children cause he is so scared and timid. He would love to find a forever home where he can get lots of lovins and feel safe. His adoption fee is $200.00If interested in adopting a pet from our shelter, please click on one of the following links which will take you to our adoption application. The shelter staff is busy and not often able to answer phone calls so please email us at rchumane@zoominternet.net with any questions. Thank you for your interest! (If you send an email or application our promise is to respond within 24 hours but most of the time it's a much shorter wait. animal.description:
Miss Lady's story:

Miss Lady has came all the way from Puerto Rico to find her new home! Despite her tough past life of living on the streets, Miss Shady Lady is full of love, life and energy! It is our hope that we can find a happy, loving home for her.

Miss Lady knows lots of tricks like sit, down, paw, high-five, come and stay. She gives soft, gentle kisses and always has a big smile on her face. She is eager to please, and loves to go for runs! She would do best in an active household, that has lots of room for her to run, play and do all the things that makes a dog happy!

Are you the perfect forever home for Miss Lady?

Age: 1 year

Gender: F

Spayed/neutered: Yes

Weight: 58lbs

Vaccines: Rabies, Distemper

Heartworm results: Negative

Lyme results: Negative

Allergies: None known

OK with kids: No small children

OK with cats: Unknown

OK with dogs: Unknown

Likes & dislikes: Likes to spin in circles when excited, loves pupperoni,

Adoption fee: $150

To Apply:

1) Print adoption application here:

https://staffordspca.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Stafford_SPCA_Adoption_Application_Adoption-Process-04182018.pdf

2) Email to adopt@staffordspca.org OR Fax to 866-522-8042.

Please see our website for details on our adoption process, and feel free to email with any questions about the process or about the pet you're interested in.

Home visits required and dog adoptions often do require structural fencing. (We make decisions regarding the fencing requirement on a dog-by-dog basis, according to the dog's exercise needs and energy level.)
Stafford SPCA does not condone the exclusive use of invisible fencing.
We reserve the right to deny placement of puppies and kittens into homes with children under 5 years old.

If you can't adopt, please sponsor me!

You can also volunteer; Get more information at www.staffordspca.org

animal.description:
Sunshine is a 29 pound, 3 year old beagle that was surrendered with her sister Susie when they both flunked out of rabbit hunting school. While she is not going to give Elmer Fudd a run for his money, she most certainly could find a chicken nugget hidden in the house in 15 seconds flat! Sunshine walks nicely on the leash, and she is working on her potty training. She doesn’t mind being crated and she is SUPER food motivated but doesn’t have any food guarding issues. She will need regular exercise and to have her food intake carefully monitored because she would gladly eat her weight in dog food three times over daily. She really enjoys the company of other playful dogs so she would be happiest in a home with another dog (or her sister Susie). As is typical for a beagle, she will also follow an interesting scent anywhere so she will need a fenced yard or to remain on leash to keep her from  following her little nose off into far away places.

This dog is spayed, up to date on vaccinations and current on flea/tick and heartworm preventative.  This dog has tested negative for heartworms.  The adoption fee is $450 if your adoption is prepaid and final prior to your dog's arrival. An additional $50 will be charged on dogs that are picked up from our Southbury CT adoption center, adopted at an event or foster home. This additional fee is necessary in order to comply with CT HB 5368.
If you are a MA resident, your new family member is required to go through a mandatory 48 hour quarantine period at our Woburn MA isolation facility.  Your new family member will be dropped off by our transport on Thursday and will be ready for you to pick him/her up on Saturday between 12pm-2pm.  An additional $100 fee will be added for any dogs picked up from the Woburn MA quarantine facility.  This additional fee is necessary in order to comply with MA Order 405-CD-12 and Order 1-AHO-05. 

TO APPLY PLEASE GO TO  www.cprdogs.com.  If your application was successfully submitted you will get a confirmation.  

After receipt of your application, an adoption counselor will then be in touch to answer your questions about this pup, discuss the adoption process and get the ball rolling!  If you have not heard from one of our volunteers within 5 days of submitting your application, please email mollibo@gmail.com.

Relinquished by his owner, King is an exceptional dog, who was unfortunately not given the time and care that he needed. He spent the majority of his time in a kennel, which is not ideal considering he enjoys spending his time being active. Brought in by a woman who got King for her son but things did not go as planned and King was not receiving the attention he needed and deserved. Being so young, he is smart and very receptive to training which is fortunate for a family who is willing to give him the love and care needed. He loves to be the center of attention and is a huge fan of belly rubs and scratches. King has been neutered, vaccinated including Rabies, wormed, tested for heartworm, and Micro-chipped.

Note:  To adopt, you must live within approximately 100 miles of one of our adoption sites (Benld, O'Fallon or Springfield IL), and be at least 18 years of age.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Maya! I was rescued by a shelter in Georgia before arriving at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue. I am a truly beautiful and sweet girl who just wants your love. I like to play with all other dogs, regardless of their size, and I think that I could make an excellent family pet for any family with children. I'd be a perfect pick for a first-time adopter who's just looking for a loveable, quiet, and clean girl to add to their family. I could be very happy residing in any type of home, whether it is in an apartment, a big house with a yard, or a farm. Either a busy or quiet lifestyle would be just fine by me, as long as we can have plenty of snuggle time! I may be the type of pup that you can bring out and about with you in public, if you wanted to. I appear to be mostly potty-trained and I love to go for long leashed walks around the ranch.

animal.description:
Meet Tallulah!!

This stunning Bloodhound girl is ready for a home of her own!  Tallulah came to us on New Years Day with her baby boy (Toutant-Beauregard aka BUBBA) and has done her job raising this big old pup!!

Tallulah is absolutely beautiful -  she is a big girl and preference to potential adopters with breed experience will be given -  BIG DOG experience is a MUST and a FENCED yard is an absolute must for this girl.

Tallulah is friendly, sweet, happy and appears to be housetrained (we cannot guarantee this - but she NEVER messes in her crate).

Tallulah gets along with other dogs her size, but honestly, would probably be happier as an only dog so she can get all the attention!!

Her photo's don't do her justice - she is a stunning example of her breed!   

Meet and greet with approved application ONLY -  please apply ONLY if you have large dog experience and a fenced yard -  bloodhound breed experience is preferred.

Adoption fee is $275 and includes all vetting.  She has been spayed, has her current rabies certificate, has been heartworm tested and has all her vaccines completed.  She also comes microchipped with a lifetime registration.

Hurry - she won't last long!!

Visit our website www.alldogscomefromheaven.com where you will find the link for adoption applications at the top right on the page.

animal.description:
Benny is in foster in Olympia, WA with Shaynes fosters. We foster dogs for TX rescues in W WA. 

This is a courtesy posting for Hay Dude Equine rescue. Yes, they also rescue HORSES!~!!!

He would be a great addition to a home that wants a love muffin snuggler lap dog ! NO young /small children that scares most small dogs., See his very detailed description below!

Thank you for wanting to adopt! Our application can be found at haydudeequine.org

If you have any problems with the application link please email jminarcin@hartjobs.com

Adoption fee $525 includes her transport, health certificate and ALL his medical, neuter, shots, chipping etc. done by Hey Dude Equine Rescue.

  If you have issues with the application please email the rescue at the above email. . We MUST have an application first thank you. We have a very detailed description.

Hi! My name is Benny! I am a super sweet boy, and love pretty much everyone I meet, I just take a little time to warm up. I show no aggression towards anything or anyone ever . I weigh approx. 10 or 11 pounds.  I am at the very most 4 years old (what the vets who examined me have said). Maybe I’m younger? They do not know. I am a total lap dog. I love being on your lap and I will be very quiet and easy and just sleep there w/o disturbing you. My foster home says I am so wonderful I have not pottied at all in the house!

I can be a little shy with new people, but will be their best friend soon! I was saved by my rescue from a hoarding case in south Texas. There were over 70 of us dogs in a little house with 2 humans. When foster mom got me, I had never even seen grass before! Even though I was not exposed to much in my early days, I am very human centric.  I am great with puppies and other small dogs, I haven’t met BIG dogs! I love love my humans and graze when I’m hungry. Im not a big eater and just love hanging out with my humans and will sleep on your lap if you let me. 
Please a winter coat and rain coat would be great for me in the PNW.

I am a pretty white and brown likely chihuahua terrier mix. . I sleep in a crate unless you allow me on your bed/furniture!!!  and get on and off the furniture. Please make sure the furniture is not too high so when i jump down I don't get injured. Even though everything is so new, I get along  great with all I have met. I do understand no , so if you don’t allow your dog on the furniture just tell me no. If you don’t want a dog on your lap then I’m not the right dog because I do love human laps! 

I am a professional snuggler. I love other dogs, and do ok with kids as long as they are older kids, dog savvy and gentle with me. NO little kids they are too enthusiastic sometimes in their snuggle efforts, so I would do best in a home with kids over the age of approximately 8 or 10. Depends on the children. However a quieter home is likely best for me.

 I am so deserving of a forever after. Please apply to adopt me

animal.description:
My name is Grace, but you can call me anything you want. Know why? Because I won't hear you; I'm deaf! But it's no big deal because I'll stay close to you and watch you carefully. You can 'talk' to me with hand signals. My foster mom says I'm the sweetest, calmest Rat Terrier around. (Since I'm around 7 years old, the indiscretions and misbehaviors of youth are a thing of the past.) I'm a good girl, who knows how to sit for treats and who walks like a dream on leash. I'm also house-trained and crate trained. I get along fabulously with all the inhabitants of my foster home, including the other Rattie, the big dog, the cat, the guinea pig, and the young human. In fact, I like just about everyone I meet. And best of all, at 18 lbs., I excel at being a lap dog. Do you have a lap for me? You can find more photos of me at https://imageevent.com/newrattitude/gracenc .
Our adoption fee is $175 for adult dogs or $225 for puppies under 6 months old.

If you are interested in adopting this dog,
PLEASE READ THE DETAILED ADOPTION PROCESS information on our website
at www.
NewRattitude.org/adopt/

From there, you can access our adoption application or contact our Adoption Team for more info.

Max won't require a lot in the way of exercise; shorter walks to explore and sniff will suffice. He would definitely love a soft bed and blankets to snuggle into while hanging out with his people. He's been neutral about seeing other dogs, and would probably do best in a home with other mellow dogs or by himself. 

Max is a medium to large sized mixed breed, approximately 7 years young, and is full grown at 44 pounds. 

Please email: adopt@gigis.org to inquire or apply to adopt this special, handsome guy!

animal.description:
Meet Cherry (aka Lilly), a sweet, beautiful girl looking for her furever home!  

Lilly is getting along well with her foster's resident dog.  She plays well with the neighborhood children ages 5 and up, walks well on leash and is house-trained!  She loves car rides and just hanging our with her humans!  She isn't a fan of her crate, but has proven to not be destructive when left alone.  And...she talks back to you! I included a video of her "talking" to her foster mom, it is VERY cute!  

Lilly came to us very underweight and emaciated.  With some TLC she has gained some weight and is doing very well.  For the time being, she should be fed small amounts of food and water throughout the day.  Since she was not fed much in her previous home, she will eat too fast and cause her stomach to become upset.  She needs to slowly get her tummy used to eating on a regular basis.

This poor girl has obviously had a rough few years behind her, but she is still a sweetheart in spite of it.  She will make a wonderful addition to your family! 


Apply at: http://caninehumane.org/adoption-application/



Adoption Fee is $350
She is up to date on vaccines and has had a wellness exam, heartworm tested and micro-chipped.

Applications are required before meeting a dog. To fill out an application go to
 http://caninehumane.org/adoption-application/ 

IF THE DOG IS ON PETFINDER IT IS STILL AVAILABLE

www.caninehumane.org

***BE SURE TO CHECK YOUR SPAM/PROMOTION EMAIL FOLDER FOR CHN RESPONSE TO YOUR APPLICATION***

There is an adoption process along with a donation.


Please bring your dog (if you have one), and a martingale collar with a leash, should we move forward.  We recycle theirs for the next dog :)  I have attached a picture of a martingale collar.  If you cannot find one, we do sell them at the daycare for 10-15.  Purchasing one from us allows us to fit it properly and it helps to benefit the rescue.  We carry leashes too, the collar and leash set are 30.  Adoption donations vary depending on the dog's age and medical expenses.  Typically they start at 650 and go up from there.  We realize this is a larger donation, however we have no state funding like shelters do.  That being said, dogs do come to you fully vetted.  They have been fixed, given distemper, bordetella, rabies, heartworm tested, de-wormed, on prevention for heartworm, fleas, ticks, intestinal parasites and microchipped.  Additionally we have paid for the microchip registration for life. 

*Please note we make every effort to have our dogs altered prior to adoption, if we cannot spay/neuter clauses will be in the contract.

*Please come down to the Dog Gone Inn in Manlius to meet us!

Thank you for choosing rescue! 

Don't forget to like us and follow us on Facebook, we get new animals in regularly.

*Please submit an application here: http://goo.gl/forms/XPuk6w9615GXqo0x2 and come down to the Dog Gone Inn in Manlius to see me or (315) 728-9344 or www.DogGoneInn.com or DogGoneInn@Yahoo.com or www.facebook.com/DogGoneInn

animal.description:
TO CONTACT THE FOSTER HOME, email applications@acdra.org. DO NOT use the Petfinder form. Inquiries don't reach us.

Meet Summit! A 5 month old male Red Heeler!  Summit is 35lbs & still growing! His name is a great indicator of one of his favorite activities, hiking. Summit also enjoys lounging & quiet time, structured leash walks, training/learning new commands, playing with a softy, fetch, belly rubs, & getting kibble out of his kong.  Although Summit enjoys and is fast friends with humans & dogs alike, he’d be best as the only dog in the household. Once Summit has bonded with his adopter and established a solid recall, he might enjoy off leash walks and play with other dogs.

Summit has a great temperament, lots of energy, is curious about the world, & is very smart. He is crate trained, housebroken & knows basic commands.  Sit, lay, drop, leave it, are ones he has down pretty well. We have Summit sit before he eats his meals & he waits until he is told to "get it". He is working on stay & his recall is great! Summit’s manners will need continued work, as with any heeler puppy.  He practices sitting before exiting doors, eyes, & responds well to his name on walks. We are working on his leash pulling & so far he is doing incredible in public places. He is able to pass people no problem. Summit will need help with his leash reactivity on walks when he sees other dogs and when in the car. Positive reinforcement & redirection seem to be key.  He’s a quick learner & I am sure with time he will be a great companion to jog or run with. He has not been socialized with cats or small children.

Summit is a really incredible dog! He needs human companions who will exercise him & train him regularly. If exposed to new experience in an intentional & timely way, I am sure he will be able to go anywhere & be comfortable in many situations standing proudly by your side. 

Summit will be adopted on a neuter contract.  He also is microchipped and up to date on age-appropriate vaccines. Summit is being fostered in Cambridge, NY. Please email applications@acdra.org with any questions.

COMPLETE AN APPLICATION
http://www.acdra.org/adoption-application

All interested people should submit an adoption application as their first step.

Marnie is a very sweet but very shy 5 yr old beagle. She was found in the south with 7 newborn puppies, whom whe was an excellent mother to. All of the puppies got adopted, and Marnie stayed to be surrogate mother to additional litters with no mother. She is quiet, and she love love loves to shred her stuffed animal toys but doesn't mess with anything in the house that isn't hers. Marnie is housebroken and loves to be outside (when it's not snowing)! She pulls very hard on leash, and we don't think she had much experience with being leash walked in her life. A fenced-in yard is a must for her. She warms up to women most easily but is suspicious of men. We feel she may have had some trauma at the hands of a man at some point in her life, so a female home is ideal for her. However, she currently has a foster dad who she is fond of but also weary of him at times. She has never growled, or even raised a lip at a human though. When she encounters someone she is shy around, she finds her bed and lays down preferring to be left alone. Fireworks and loud noises also send her cowering, but if you are willing to give her some time, she returns your patience with lots of love! Her favorite thing is following her foster mom around and hanging out next to her desk when she works. She is great with all dogs (very submissive) and is currently living with 4 of them. We feel living with other dogs is beneficial to Marnie so she can gain confidence. If you are looking for a sweet, easy dog who just needs some time, please check out Marnie!

All pets adopted from GDHS are spayed or neutered, have vaccinations brought up to date, are on heartworm preventative (dogs), FIV/FELV tested (cats) and microchipped.

animal.description:
Dobby - Male
Lab/Hound Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 10/21/2020
Current weight 16lbs

FENCED IN YARD RECOMMENDED 
Not recommending homes with small children due to typical puppy jumping and nipping

Meet Dobby. He is 1 of 7 siblings surrendered to the shelter, so they all came to Illinois to find a forever home. Though from Arkansas he loves the snow and his toys. He is an energetic puppy who adores attention and a lot of love to give. He does great with everyone, kids and other dogs. He is learning basic puppy manners, crate training and potty training all of which are going well. He will need someone home (not left alone more then a few hours) to continue with these basics and socialization skills. With love and patience he will make a wonderful addition to any home.

WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS 
 
Medical included is as follows:
Spay/Neuter (age appropriate) *Forever Home uses Fox Valley Animal Welfare League in Aurora, IL
Age appropriate core vaccines
Fecal testing and deworming
Flea and tick preventative
Free 1st Vet visit at one of our participating vets
Microchipping
 
Forever Home Dog Rescue reserves the right to deny any applicant.


WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS

Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies.

THIS PET IS NOT AVAILABLE THROUGH BROTHER WOLF ANIMAL RESCUE. 
PLEASE CONTACT THE OWNER FOR MORE INFORMATION OR TO MAKE AN APPLICATION FOR ADOPTION. 

The owner's email is: michellethecrittersitter@gmail.com

Bobbi Jo has only been with my family for a very short time. We rescued her from a shelter and was told she was good with dogs, cats, and children but found out very quickly she is not okay with being friends with a cat. I have a feeling she may have been a coon dog at one point in her life and I think cats symbolize a small prey animal too much for her to ever reconsider being friends with one. She has however been magnificent with both of my young children and my older large breed dog. She has quickly become quite the bed bug and lazy girl. She is amazing in the crate and doesn't make a peep. Potty training would be the only challenge for this sweet girl. I don't think she's ever lived inside but is very smart and I'm sure will pick it up rather quickly. If your looking for a low energy couch potato, she is your kinda gal! (NO CATS)

animal.description:
We saw Tigger, a 70 lbs Boxer/Pit mix,  being surrendered to the city shelter as we were rescuing another dog. We could see what a sweet gentle soul he is (Tigger calmly greeted the dog we were saving with soft body language and accepted petting happily) that we came back the very next day and got him. And boy are we glad we did. He is THE perfect dog - the total package. He's great with people, dogs and kids. He absolutely loves to snuggle with you anywhere, anytime and enjoys the company of of all pups big and small (he's fostered with two resident dogs and they get along great -- even the shy one).

Tigger also enjoys a good frolic in the park and long walks he's great for the outdoorsy/active types. But, he's super calm while at home. Despite being neglected in his previous home -- he sustained an eye injury that went untreated and he now has limited vision in that eye -- he is the happiest, most open hearted dog you could meet. We will make the perfect family pet. Inquire about Tigger today!

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in one of our Hero Babies!  Before inquiring, we thought it was important to share a few of our policies.  

Puppies - We do not adopt puppies under 16 weeks to out of state adopters.  This is due to our spay/neuter policies, and all dogs must be spayed/neutered before leaving Georgia state lines.  We do not adopt siblings to the same household.  

Your Current Pets - We do require that all of your current dogs and cats are current on vaccines and spayed/neutered.  

Adoptions - We do not have a shelter and are a foster-home based organization. We do require that you have an approved adoption application to schedule a meet and greet. You can fill out an adoption application on our website, www.herorescue.org/adopt. Once your application is approved it will be sent to the foster family that is currently caring for the dog. They will be able to provide information on likes, dislikes, personality, etc. They will also schedule a time for you to meet the dog. We do require a homecheck prior to adoption.

Inquiries - If you would like more information on any dogs in the rescue, please email us at info@herorescue.org.

You can make an appointment to meet available dogs at our ADOPTION CENTER by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet and available cats at MEOW PALACE by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1. 

For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with the next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE: http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Leo is a sweet boy from a rural shelter in VA. Leo can be shy with meeting new people but once he warms up to you he is your best friend! Due to Leo's shy behavior he would prefer a home with no kids under the age of 15 years old! Leo loves other dogs and loves to play! Leo has shown some signs of separation anxiety so he will need a home that is willing and able to work on it with him so he feels more comfortable being alone! 

Adoption Coordinator: Katie R
Location: Foster Home

Includes spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital, and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

Hi – I’m Scout 

I am a big lovable lug who is very smart and loves food so easy to train. 
I am an active and happy puppy that loved playing with my siblings.   I am doing well on housebreaking and house rules.  I have learned to go outside when a bell is rung and come in to a whistle where I sit right inside the door – and get a treat. 
I love to play with any toy around and I don’t mind the cold and snow at all.  
The resident cat looks really interesting and I wish he would play with me but I can be distracted. 

Will you be the family to love me and teach me everything I need to learn ?  

Go to Spotslaststop.org  to fill out an application if you would like to meet me.
Note: We consider potential adopters only after an application has been submitted.  A PetFinder inquiry could slow that process down.  A dog will be set to Adoption Pending once we have at least 3 valid applications.

Note:  Puppies this young will not be adopted outside of Minnesota.

animal.description:
Dash - Male
Lab/Hound Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 10/21/2020
Current weight 16lbs

FENCED IN YARD RECOMMENDED 
Not recommending homes with small children due to typical puppy jumping and nipping

Meet Dash. He is 1 of 7 siblings surrendered to the shelter, so they all came to Illinois to find a forever home. Though from Arkansas he loves the snow and his toys. He is an energetic puppy who adores attention and a lot of love to give. He does great with everyone, kids and other dogs. He is learning basic puppy manners, crate training and potty training all of which are going well. He will need someone home (not left alone more then a few hours) to continue with these basics and socialization skills. With love and patience he will make a wonderful addition to any home.

WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS 
 
Medical included is as follows:
Spay/Neuter (age appropriate) *Forever Home uses Fox Valley Animal Welfare League in Aurora, IL
Age appropriate core vaccines
Fecal testing and deworming
Flea and tick preventative
Free 1st Vet visit at one of our participating vets
Microchipping
 
Forever Home Dog Rescue reserves the right to deny any applicant.

animal.description:
Breed: Labrador Retriever (purebred)
Sex: Spayed Female
DOB: 04/13/2020
Weight: 51 lbs
Energy Level: Medium
Personality Type: Affectionate, Well-Mannered, Playful, Social, Happy
History: Owner Surrender
Good With: Dogs, Kids 8+ Yrs
Ideal Home: Active person family without young kids! No apartments!
Fence Requirements: Preferred
Special Info: Nala is well behaved, already housebroken, and has been well cared for since birth!

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Cassie is a young dog with lots of puppy energy and love to give! This sweet girl was picked up as a local stray and sat waiting in the shelter for someone to claim her to no avail.

In her foster home she is working on her basic manners and social skills. She loves to play ball and can keep herself occupied while chewing on a bone. Being full of personality, Cassie does have a few bad habits, but she is working on getting better every day!

Cassie is crate trained, but is still working on her potty training when she is loose in the house. She LOVES everyone she meets, but can be a bit nervous in unfamiliar environments. Cassie does best with dogs her size or larger. She has met a few cats and is curious, but does not fixate on them. Cassie's perfect home would have kids over the age of 12 or an active family who wants a dog that can keep up with them during the day, but snuggle up on the couch at night.

Please fill out an application if you would like to add this perfect girl to your family! Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

animal.description:
Courage is a 1 1/2 year old male Chesapeake Bay Retriever mix that came to us as a stray.  There had been multiple sightings of him as he roamed the countryside on his own where he learned to defend himself from other dogs and other unknown predators.  He was not as easy catch as life on his own had taught him to run away first and ask questions later!  Now that he is safe, he is very glad for human attention, but other dogs make him nervous and we think he would be happiest as the only dog in the family.  He will need time and patience and we recommend no children under the age of 10.  Courage weighs 70 lbs. and will need a fenced yard so he knows his roaming days are over.

I love to cuddle and get belly rubs and will paw at the door to let you know I need to go out to potty! My huge smile lets you know I am a happy dog. I hope you will let me put my smile on your face, too. I do best as only pet or with dog similar size as me. No cats or small dogs. Love, Rocky.



I qualify for Foster First, which means you can foster me for 14 days prior to adoption to ensure I'm the perfect fit for your family!

animal.description:
Angus
Male
11 months
60lbs
Catahoula Leopard Dog 

If big dogs are your thing, then Angus is sure to impress! He absolutely adores everyone he meets. Angus hasn't had a single accident inside his foster home. He lives with dogs, cats and kids and is an equal opportunity playmate for all! Angus walks great on leash and takes treats like the gentleman he is. He loves playing with toys and loves taking his pick out of the toy bin. Angus sleeps in his crate at night but would prefer a nice comfy bed instead. This big guy has a lot of energy and is looking for an active family to take walks with and to play with and if you have an emtpy lap, he may even try to sit in it. Angus loves to love and give kisses, he just may be the Valentine you've been missing!

If you are interested in Angus please apply at https://www.nickelcitycaninerescue.org/adopt-a-dog or message the rescue if you are already pre-approved.

animal.description:
Cooper
4 years 
45 lbs
Male
Red border collie mix

Meet Cooper! This handsome boy came all the up from Texas to steal someones heart just in time for Valentines day! Cooper is a big ole teddy bear who will crawl right up onto your lap if you let him. He LOVES being outside and going for walks and does really well on a leash. He would do great with an active family and one with a canine brother or sister to play with would be even better! Because he forgets his size sometimes, a family with older children would be best for him but he is overall very gentle and sweet. 

Cooper has had hardly any accidents in his foster home and has been doing great learning some basic commands. Hes a silly boy and might try to steal a slipper or two when youre not looking, but overall seems to understand and respond well to no. He loves his toys, napping next to his foster mom while she works and watching out the window throughout the day. He is crate trained and neutered. 

His foster moms favorite thing about him is how he thinks hes a lap dog and will scoot up right next to you or on you when hes got the chance! 

If you are interested in Cooper please apply at https://www.nickelcitycaninerescue.org/adopt-a-dog or message the rescue if you are already pre-approved.

animal.description:
Penelope is a chi mix who is about a year old and 11 pounds. She may have applications in progress but is currently available. Penelope is a shy girl, but just bursting with love when she warms up. If you're looking for a sweetheart of a lap dog, she's well worth the wait of letting her get to know you at her pace. She is blossoming in her foster home, and coming out of her shell more each day. 

After some slow introductions with her foster fur siblings, Penelope is now happy to play and enjoys it. She is equally happy to snuggle in your lap all day though. This pretty girl is potty trained and would do best with a secure fenced in yard to help her comfort level and prevent her from escaping if she gets spooked. She also needs a home without small children as their unpredictable nature can scare her. And while she's a worthy and happy playmate for other dogs when properly introduced, she can be too rough with kitties, so should have only canine fur siblings. 

Because of her lack of confidence and fearful nature, she will need a fur friend. She takes their cues and really needs one to learn that the world isn't so scary . With that said, she will need decompression for a day or two, with a new friend, and slow intros. Because even new friends are scary at first. Once shes settled in, she's great and will follow their lead! 

Adoption fee is $300 and includes spay/neuter, microchip, fecal/deworming, vaccines and prevention up to date. Ohio residents only.

   be considered for adoption of any of our precious rescues.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gVIaha9F_BLDJqwlbWJsjDs40B-jDo7M/view?usp=sharing

   DOWNLOAD / EDIT / SUBMIT to LI.saveadogaday@gmail.com.
   Include in subject line: DOG NAME / APPLICATION / YOUR NAME

2.  Matilde is STILL AVAILABLE for adoption if you see her posting. We 
     promptly update when our pups are adopted. No need to email asking.

     As we are an all volunteer rescue operating with a shortfall of volunteers, we 
    may NOT BE ABLE TO REPLY TO INDIVIDUAL INQUIRIES in a timely manner, 
    HOWEVER... please know that each and every APPLICATION SUBMITTED is 
    thoroughly looked at and considered.

3. A fully fenced yard is necessary for adopting any of our precious rescue pups. 
    Homes with electric fences will not be considered for adoption.


Meet little Matilde.... 6 week old Jack Russell Terrier and just the cutest little thing.

Matilde will be arriving, with her brother Spud, at the end of the month. We hope to have the pups forever families waiting to welcome them home.

It is always appropriate to consider the needs of the pups breed that you will be welcoming to your family. Thank you.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Name: China

DOB: 12/24/2014

Weight: 5lbs

Adoption Fee: 300.00

Hey everyone! My name is China. I came from Texas originally.

From Her Texas Foster:

China is very shy and afraid and will need time to warm up to her new family.

She is timid and shy and will need a patient family that will allow her to warm up and come out of her shell. She is afraid of being touched at first, but after a few weeks she is ok being held. She came with another dog and follows him for confidence, due to that she will require another confident dog in her forever home. The first week she did not want to eat, but eventually and with enough bribery she ate.

She will need a family that is willing to give her the time and patience to be the best version of herself. Due to her shyness a fenced in yard will also be required in order to keep her safe.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

Please check out our website,

www.ruffstartrescue.org

for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals!

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

animal.description:
Bert is a handsome, hyper, Weimaraner looking for Weimar savvy people to call his new family. He is your typical Weimar, so he's looking for people who have experience with his breed so they know what they're getting in to and will love his quirks. Bert's favorite activity is fetch, and he gets a bit intense when playing. He would probably play fetch all day as long as someone is there to throw the ball! He's looking for an active home that can give him ALL the exercise and training. He will need some work on his basic manners, as well as self control and management for potential toy guarding. Bert wants to be with his people as much as possible due to his separation anxiety. Bert is picky with the dog friends he wants to make. He would enjoy having a smaller, relaxed, dog friend. Bert also wouldn't mind living with dog savvy kids aged 12+ or kitties. He is not appropriate for apartment living. 
Have an inquiry? Want to adopt? Please complete our brief online application here and we will email you back ASAP: 
https://www.popememorialspca.org/how-to-adopt

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is Jasper and I’m waiting and hoping for a forever home.  You see, one day I found myself wandering all alone.  I think my people went off and left me, but I don’t know why because I do try my best to be a good boy.  Lucky for me, a kind person came along and brought me to this rescue and now I’m safe in my nice foster home where I’m getting lots of TLC till I find  a family that will never leave me on my own again.
 
Here are some things I can tell you about me:  I’m about 1 year old and weigh in at 55 pounds.  My breed is a best guess, but my foster mom says I am a hound mix.  She tells me whatever I am doesn’t matter because I’m a handsome, lovable boy.  That makes me happy.  I am house trained, crate trained and coming along nicely with my leash training.  I like to please my humans and I listen well.  I am not fostered with children, but I’m an easy going boy with medium energy and I love all people so I think I’d enjoy having kids in my family.  They should be over 5 because I’m still young yet and wouldn’t want to get too playful around little ones.  I also get along great with other dogs and behave well around cats.
 
You’ll be glad to know that I am neutered and up to date on my vaccinations.  I’m also micro-chipped and on monthly flea/tick and heart worm preventative.  My doggy bag is packed and I’m so excited to get the word that my forever home has been found.  If you think I may be the boy for you, please email Laurie at lovelabs816@gmail.com for an application and she’ll send one right out to you.  My adoption fee is $400.  Can’t wait to meet you!
 
Like us on facebook: https://www.facebook.com/PawsClawsNewEngland
Follow/tag us on Instagram: @pawsclawsne or #pawsclawsne

Laurie Terebesi
Adoption Coordinator Northeast Region
lovelabs816@gmail.com

animal.description: Ryder is an approximately 10-year-old Lab mix.  Ryder's a victim in a different way of Covid-19.  Ryder's owner had Covid and was unable to continue to care for him due to the Covid lingering effects.  When we were contacted Ryder had gone to stay with friends but they only allowed him to stay in the cold garage, which was not what Ryder's owner wanted for him.  Ryder's owner contacted us and asked if we would be able to take him and find him a new home so that he wasn't staying in a cold and lonely garage.  Ryder was thought to be a Lab/Rottie mix, but he is a very smaller sized lab.  Unfortunately, his tail was docked when he was young,  He is a very sweet boy who even smiles at you.  He needs a home with a loving family who will allow him to be part of the family.  No more being left outside where he will bark out of frustration from being lonely.  Ryder is active and in great physical shape.  If you are looking for a companion who is very loving, easygoing, enjoys walks, playing fetch, and cuddling on the couch, Ryder may be a great match for you.  If you are interested in meeting Ryder or learning more about him, please go to our website, goldenrescue.com.  Please read our adoption process and then complete the online application. https://www.goldenrescue.com/adoption-process/ Please note we DO NOT adopt outside the state of Colorado.

animal.description:
IMPORTANT: Please do not do an inquiry through Petfinder, our volunteers do not have time to reply to the inquiries. Please visit our website to learn more about our adoption process at newhoperescue.org. 

This dog is being fostered with New Hope Dog Rescue (Saskatoon).  If you are interested in adopting please fill out an Adoption Application. Meet and greets are by appointment only and done so after an adoption application has been submitted. A successful applications will be contacted by the foster home to discuss further. We are volunteer run so please be patient.

Hi my name is Julez. I am about 10 weeks young. I am a mixed breed and think i will be medium to a large dog.

I can sit and lie down and “go kennel” 85 Percent of the time. I am very food motivated and take my treats gently. Actually I love my treats!

At night i stay in my crate all night without any accidents or crying.
During the day I stay in my crate for 2 hours sometime longer with no accidents. Then have a playtime outside, weather permitting. 

I am working hard at outside training but will need some additional, consistent guidance.

I have no other animals or children to play with now but i think i would be more than happy to be with a larger family. 
 
I love to meet and greet new people at my fosters clinic. They say I am very smart and after a few minutes, I am very caIm. However, when i am excited I tend to nibble and chew on my fosters hands but i am easily redirected with toys or reassurance if i stop.
    
I do have lots of energy but i am a puppy, once I play and do some training I am completely happy to lie on my mat and chew on a toy while I hang out with my fosters. I am very calm and love to snuggle close to my foster people. 

Julez has been microchipped, dewormed, current on age appropriate vaccines and has received a health check from a vet. adoption fee is $495 (200 is refunded upon proof of spay).

To view more dogs go to http://www.newhoperescue.org/adopt/available-dogs/

Disclaimer: in most cases we are guessing the breed mix. These are best guesses on our part. For puppies it can be extremely difficult and we are also guessing on what size they will be. 

NEW HOPE DOG RESCUE is not a shelter. Our dogs are placed in loving foster homes. WE NEED FOSTER HOMES TO HELP MORE DOGS - CONTACT US TODAY!!!
Definitions:
Pending - means that we are working through the adoption process with the 1st applicant. We usually don't add the pending until we are pretty sure the adoption will go through (like at the home visit stage)
Adopted - you know!! A happy ending for a homeless dog.

animal.description:
CLARKSVILLE, MISSOURI (St Louis area)

Looking for a loving forever home. Comes with current vet records, no-pull harness, leash, and some of his current food. He is also neutered and microchipped. 

Zeus has been raised with a littermate which has caused him to wander and not always return when called. Especially if he and his brother were loose together. 

On leash, he is very well behaved and enjoys going on walks. He is an outdoor dog and has successfully been around goats, a calf, ducks, chickens, and cats. They do seem to successfully keep coyotes and other predators away from our property even though they are confined to a paddock or tethered run. 

Zeus is also familiar with adults and kids. Does not exhibit any bad behaviors around humans. Has spent some daytime hours indoors, but has never spent the night in a house. 

Zeus is still at an impressionable age of 3 and can be used as a working guardian dog or a family pet with additional obedience training.

animal.description:
This is Maxine, she is a 12 week old Pittie/lab x puppy, she weighs approximately 17 lbs.  Maxine came into rescue with her brother after being tossed in a field in AL. They were found by nice lady who brought the puppies into her home and drove them to TN.    Maxine is a very happy and snugly little girl.  Typical puppy, working on potty training and crate training.  Interested applicants should fill out an application!    

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
My name is Bubba and I am about 5 years old.  First thing ….my ears! I have the most adorable ears.  If you are looking to meet new friends, my ears will be a great conversation starter, or you can just admire them yourself.  I’m a good boy. I have been in a loving foster home, but I would really like a forever family of my very own.  I’m medium to large sized weighing about 65 pounds of unconditional love. ’m a friendly boy who loves all people.  Sometimes when I get excited I will jump, so I’d probably be best with kids 9+ unless they are dog savvy.  I listen well though and when told no, I will stop.  I am food motivated, smart and eager to please so a little direction could remedy that.  Otherwise, I’m a mellow energy boy who is cuddly and loves giving kisses.  I enjoy being up on the sofa or in bed snuggling.  I’m goofy and playful and also love going on adventures with my person in the great outdoors, as you can see from my pictures.  I’m crate trained, housetrained and I’ve even been neutered, up to date on my shots, so I’m ready to go.  I’m just looking for a loving family of my very own who will play with me and love me as much as I will love them.  I’ll give you the best kisses and cuddles you’ve ever had.  Check out my pictures, I’m adorable and again, those ears!  If you want to know more about me or meet me in person please contact Martina Animal Rescue at martinaanimalrescue@gamil.com.
Love, Bubba

animal.description:
Due to COVID-19 precautions, all animals for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. Copy and paste the link to access the sign-up genius for an appointment: https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet for dogs and https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1 for cats.

For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to AdoptionCenter@homewardtrails.org.

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE:
http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

This handsome, happy dog is Mark. He is a friendly 3 1/2 year old mixed breed dog. He is 60 lbs. Mark is a nice dog and he gets along with other dogs. He is not at all a fan of cats. 

Mark is at Homeward Trails Adoption Center in Fairfax Station and is eager to meet you. 

Mark was brought to a rural shelter as a stray before coming to Homeward Trails. 

Adoption Coordinator: Adoption Center 
Location: Adoption Center

The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program.

animal.description:
IMPORTANT!!!   All adoptions are by appointment only going forward and are spaced 30 minutes apart. PLEASE call the shelter directly during business hours for more information (see number below).  You need to make sure that the animal in which you have an interest is still available and to set up an appointment to meet the specific animal.  Once you arrive at the shelter for your scheduled appointment, please follow the directions that you were given over the telephone. If you are running late for your appointment or will be unable to make your scheduled appointment time, notify staff immediately. This will enable them to schedule that time for another prospective adoptive family. If necessary, they will be able to reschedule your appointment to a more convenient time.  

ZEKE Is a happy, smiling Aussie mix dog. His age is listed as 1 to 2 years and he weighs 48 pounds. He is mostly a creamy white color with touches of tan and black markings. This is another dog that staff really likes. They think he is a doll! Unfortunately, he has not yet been neutered. So, please read the important information below. Then, call the shelter staff to schedule an adoption appointment if you would like to add this boy to your family.

Adoption fees are $80 for dogs.  Cat adoption fees are $50. Cash or check only. Please be sure to take the exact amount with you. 

NOTE: All shelter fees are under review and may be changed or modified at any time without advance notice.

The shelter routinely vaccinates all healthy appearing animals upon their arrival at the shelter and deworms them.  Any animals not already spayed/neutered must have the procedure done through the veterinary clinic that contracts with the county before that animal can be released from the clinic to the new family. By state law, animals old enough to be given a rabies vaccine, must have that vaccine done, as well.  The vaccine is given by the veterinary clinic staff at a separate cost to the adoptive family. 

Hold periods for every incoming animal vary for several reasons including, but not limited to, whether the animal came in from the Cumberland County area, or from the City of Crossville, which contracts with the county for its animal shelter services.  Check with the staff to verify the availability date of every animal for which you have an interest.

For more information on this pet, call the shelter at (931)484-8525. The shelter is open Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday from 10am to 2pm. Closed Wednesday and Sunday and county observed holidays.

animal.description:
Sweet Ghost is a gorgeous 3 year old husky boy, who literally was saved the last minute from a highkill shelter. Ghost is very loving and super friendly, who is great with people and gets along with other dogs. He is friendly with young kids but can get anxious with sudden movement and being touched from the back, so preferably a family with older kids.  As a typical young husky, Ghost needs at least 1-2 hours of daily exercise to get his energy out, then he will be super calm, chill and mellow for the most part, His wonderful foster family recently potty trained him and taught him sit, but he definitely needs more training for other commands. Ghost is a quick learner, curious, and playful. A sweet home with other doggie friends for him to play with and a decent secure yard would be best for this energetic boy, 
Ghost is neutered, microchipped and current on vaccines. Please email Alljoy4paws@yahoo.com to spoil this precious boy!

animal.description:
Pistachio is a beautiful female German Shepherd estimated around a year of age. Pistachio was a stray therefore we do not know her history or background.

Pistachio is a sweet girl with those she knows but is very timid and unsure of new people. She can be vocal and skittish initially when meeting especially in new places. Pistachio does well going through pet stores and parks but during focused meetings she does not handle the attention well. If she is ignored and allowed to check someone out from afar first she does better but if she is rushed or has all the attention on her Pistachio will bark and be defensive. Once Pistachio gets to know someone she is an affectionate, goofy, and wicked smart girl. She loves to play, get belly rubs, and cuddle on the couch. She is going to require a lot of patience though as even with those she knows she occasionally is sure they are aliens trying to kidnap her. Please research the 'fear period' of German Shepherd behavioral development and understand that in addition to being in the midst of that stage Pistachio also has the added stress of transitions being in rescue. Pistachio loves toys - Kong's, jolly balls, and in a pinch her leash - and is figuring out the premise of fetch. Pistachio has limited experience with children 8+ years of age and given her hesitation towards new people she is not currently recommended for a home with children.

Pistachio lives with other dogs in her foster home and does a generally good job. She is unsure of new dogs and tends to be more avoidant initially. She is slowly figuring out how to play and can be a bit rough at first but is also learning how to respect the boundaries other dogs set for her. She currently lives with an adult cat and does a good job respecting her space. She has not been around any young/active cats but as of now we have no reason to think she would do poorly adjusting to a new home with cats.

Pistachio is a young girl who is looking for guidance and patience as she figures out her role in a family. She is going to require structured socialization, patience, and lots of love to help her discover the world doesn't have to be scary. If you're the home for Pistachio email tierhavenrescue@gmail.com for an adoption application or visit Tierhaven.rescuegroups.org for FAQs

animal.description:
**If a dog/pup is still listed on petfinder we are still accepting applications on him/her. We will not respond to petfinder inquiries regarding any information already publicly posted.** Please take time to read the information provided and complete an application if interested.** Incomplete applications will not be considered.**

Hi! My name is Rori! 
I am about 10 months old and I weigh around 32 pounds. I am spayed, current on vaccines, microchipped, and on heartworm and flea prevention. I am a super social girl that is looking for an active home. I am still very much a puppy and need adopters willing to continue socializing and working on all aspects of basic training to help me be the best girl I can be! 
My adoption fee is $395. 

Please submit an application if you want to make me part of your family! 
Meet and greets are scheduled with approved adopters. 
Copy the link below and paste it into your browser for an application:

http://www.emailmeform.com/builder/form/wACc22HN2JDb60dtb465Z 


Our adoption process consists of an application, and reference checks. We do home visits when a reference check is not enough. You must be at least 21 years old to apply to adopt.
Please fill out all fields as accurately as possible. We will not process incomplete applications. 

Adoptions are made on a best home basis. If two excellent applications come in for the same dog, our policy is first in time, first in line. Our goal is to have the very best home for all our dogs. Our dogs are in private foster homes waiting to be adopted. Due to limited foster space, we are unable to hold an animal to be adopted out at a later time.

Please keep in mind that we do our best to make an educated guess as to the breeds of our rescued pets. In rescue we rarely see the parents of our dogs and puppies, and even when we do, they are usually mixed breeds as well. 

We rely solely on adoption fees and donations to provide care for our rescued animals, many of whom have incurred medical bills that are much higher than any possible adoption fee. The fees received act to help support the organization as a whole, allowing them to continue efforts to rescue animals from high-kill shelters in South Carolina and Georgia.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Thanks for your interest in a pet from A.R.F.! If you see a pet here, they are still available for adoption and you should apply through our adoption application on our website at https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/
If you are looking for 1 (or 2!) fun puppies, look no further. Trinket and Triscuit are adorable 10 week old female beagle mix puppies. Trinket has an all black head and weighs in at 9 pounds. Triscuit has a white stipe on the face and weighs in at 12.5 pounds. Given their age estimate and size, they could grow to be medium sized dogs, under 50 pounds. They are currently being potty trained, but are pretty good at hitting their pee pee pads. They are super playful and friendly and LOVE the snow! They do fine with other dogs and have not been tested with cats, but are young enough to be ok. They love human interaction and belly rubs!

This pup is micro-chipped and up to date on all vaccinations, and spayed/neutered. The new family will be required to complete a basic obedience course of their choosing. The pup's adoption fee is $375. Please note ARF does not approve applications for any puppy under 6 months of age to families that live outside of Illinois and/or beyond 100 miles of Wheaton or Glen Ellyn, IL. A meeting will not be scheduled until you have an approved application, so if you're interested in adopting this pup fill out an online application today! https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/ Once your application has been approved, an ARF volunteer will contact you to arrange a meeting. ARF is an all volunteer organization. Due to a high volume of applications, we are often unable to respond to questions until your application has been approved. Thank you for your patience!

Thank you for considering a rescue pet from A.R.F.-Animal Rescue Foundation! We are
based in Wheaton, IL and conduct adoption events in the DuPage County area. If you are interested in adopting one of our pets, please submit an adoption application at https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/

Adoption appointments are scheduled based on the order of applications received, so submit your application early! Submitting an application does not commit you to any animal but does get you a head start with the adoption approval process. Due to a high volume of applications, we are often unable to respond to questions or schedule meetings until your application has been approved. More information about our adoption process can be found on our website here: https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/

As an all-volunteer, foster home-based organization, A.R.F. Animal Rescue Foundation does not have a facility where applicants can visit our animals. Please visit https://www.arf-il.org/events/ for a list of our upcoming adoption events.

Thank you for choosing to adopt, not shop!

animal.description:
Meet Ruffles! She’s a Cairn Terrier/Glen of Imaal Terrier mix estimated to be about 5 years old.
Ruffles was dumped at a Walmart parking lot with a softball size lump on her side, curled over claws, and tons of matted hair. She’s always smiling and will give sweet kisses though! Everyone is her friend!
She’s been on a weight loss journey starting at 40 pounds and losing about a pound a week (now at 36). One of her fat rolls had caused a yeast patch making her very itchy, but that’s almost gone now! The lump has been removed as well. It was found to be a SCT which is cancerous, but it’s all gone with low chances of coming back or spreading. The vet said it shouldn’t affect her length or quality of life. The removal and weight loss have given her even more vibrancy in her personality! She now plays with toys and her furry foster siblings!
This girl loves walks. She lives for walks! And she is just the friendliest wanting to say a sweet hello to all she meets, humans and dogs of all sizes. She’a also an excellent skating partner!
She’s a very well behaved pooch. She’s never had an accident. She can go just about anywhere with you which is her greatest desire! She’s been to happy hour, farmer’s market, hikes, boat rides, you name it. She likes to snuggle on the sofa too and is very content in her dog bed at night. She’s really a very adaptable dog as long as she’s with you. 
She has already been spayed and up to date on shots and is heartworm positive. She has started treatment which is covered by the rescue. 
You can see more of her foster life on Instagram: @pawsomefoster
Ruffles is ready for a furever home!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

Please call 352-486-5138 or email us at animalservices@levycounty.org.  If the dog is an owner release we may have more info on the dog. If the dog is a drop off or stray we would not have background info on him/her.

ALL adoptions are CASH ONLY...NO checks or cards.  SPAY/NEUTER PROCEDURES AND RABIES VACCINATIONS (which are both required by Florida law), along with a MICROCHIP will be given on premises before adopted animals are aloud to leave.

Dog adoptions fees are: (CASH ONLY)
Male = $40.00
Female = $55.00
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Levy County Animal Services is a rescue friendly shelter. We welcome rescue organizations to assist us with the placement of healthy adoptable pets. The requirements are described in our Placement Partner Agreement. Levy County Animal Services recognizes the benefit of networking with rescue groups. Rescues wishing a Placement Partner Agreement can download it on our website or email us at animalservices@levycounty.org and we will email you the agreement.

animal.description:
IMPORTANT!!!   All adoptions are by appointment only going forward and are spaced 30 minutes apart. PLEASE call the shelter directly during business hours for more information (see number below).  You need to make sure that the animal in which you have an interest is still available and to set up an appointment to meet the specific animal.  Once you arrive at the shelter for your scheduled appointment, please follow the directions that you were given over the telephone. If you are running late for your appointment or will be unable to make your scheduled appointment time, notify staff immediately. This will enable them to schedule that time for another prospective adoptive family. If necessary, they will be able to reschedule your appointment to a more convenient time.  

KEANO is sweet, Blue Heeler mix dog. He is about 1 to 2 years of age and his blue merle and tan markings, with a little bit of white, make him a great dog to photograph. Staff likes this dog!  He likes to reach through the bars of his kennel to kiss the hands that are held out to him!  He weighs 46 pounds and he has not yet been neutered. So, please read the important information below.  Then called to schedule an adoption appointment if you would like to meet him in person to make your adoption decision.

Adoption fees are $80 for dogs.  Cat adoption fees are $50. Cash or check only. Please be sure to take the exact amount with you. 

NOTE: All shelter fees are under review and may be changed or modified at any time without advance notice.

The shelter routinely vaccinates all healthy appearing animals upon their arrival at the shelter and deworms them.  Any animals not already spayed/neutered must have the procedure done through the veterinary clinic that contracts with the county before that animal can be released from the clinic to the new family. By state law, animals old enough to be given a rabies vaccine, must have that vaccine done, as well.  The vaccine is given by the veterinary clinic staff at a separate cost to the adoptive family. 

Hold periods for every incoming animal vary for several reasons including, but not limited to, whether the animal came in from the Cumberland County area, or from the City of Crossville, which contracts with the county for its animal shelter services.  Check with the staff to verify the availability date of every animal for which you have an interest.

For more information on this pet, call the shelter at (931)484-8525. The shelter is open Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday from 10am to 2pm. Closed Wednesday and Sunday and county observed holidays.
