animal.description:
Dolly is the most affectionate dog you will ever meet! She is never out of kisses for her people and will gladly spend all her time cuddling with you on the couch! Her love for you knows no boundaries and personal space is not something she is very familiar with! She is super dog friendly and loves playing with her foster siblings! She has a major sweet tooth and loves peanut butter treats whenever she can get them! 

Dolly was kept outside before coming to the rescue. She is house trained but has had an occasional accident when not able to go outside. Side Note: she really does not like going out in the rain!!! ? She does really well out in the house and is content to nap the day away on the couch or on her bed! She is not a big fan of crates, but we have been working with her to be ok if she needs to be in one! She is however, such a good girl that she really does not need to be in one!! She loves car rides and meeting new people! Dolly is such an incredible dog and despite everything she has been through, she is so sweet, gentle, and literally love everyone!! Dolly would be an amazing addition to any home!!

Dolly will be spayed, microchipped, up to date on vaccines prior to adoption. She is currently going through the beginning stages of heartworm treatment.  

If you are interested in adopting Dolly, fill out an application at https://www.eunoiarescue.org/adopt.

animal.description:
My name is Baby, I am a sweet and gentle 1 year old.  I have not had much attention in life, so I am also quite timid and a bit shy.  My rescuers are not sure what happened to me in the past, but they say I’m a good boy.  I don’t bark or whine and I am super easy.  I am good with other dogs and will be neutered on 2/4.  I’ve also had all my shots.  I am looking for a patient home where I will be loved and will learn that I’m safe.  I’m about 50 pounds right now, but could probably go for gaining a few more pounds.  I like people and children, but would probably do best in a home with older children or with well trained and gentle younger kids who won’t jump on me or scare me.  I do not pull on leash and although I’m a bit scared to go in my crate, I’m great and sleep like a baby once in.  I look forward to having a family of my very own who will love me, play with me and teach me that the world is not a scary place.  In return I will be a great companion and will love you unconditionally.  If you want to know more about me or meet me in person please contact Martina Animal Rescue at martinaanimalrescue@yahoo.com, or text my foster mom, Linda at (707) 326-6114
Love, Baby

She has the kindest soul and sweetest face ever. She came to us from an overcrowded shelter in the south. Hazel came to us Heartworm positive and has since had her treatment. She is on a 30 day regimen of antibiotics and steroids. She will need to be retested and started on HW prevention ASAP.
Hazel needs to go to a home where she is the only dog. 
She is spayed, UTD on Vaccinations, and Microchipped.

animal.description:
Franklin is a lovely light golden brown small dog. He stands about 20 inches tall. Do not be fooled by this little fellows age. Franklin is truly a small bundle of joy. He is quite active. He enjoys walking in the neighborhood at least twice a day. He is curious and enjoys being outside.

He can run like the wind to fetch his toy. He is playful with his toys and enjoys a good game of tug.

Franklin is friendly to other dogs that he meets while walking. 

He has not been exposed to cats, however, we do think he would do okay. 

Franklin has been around children ranging in age from 15 months to 8 years. He does just fine with children. Tolerant of their noise and fast movements. 

He settles easily in his bed at night beside mine and sleeps through the night. He is eager to meet new people. 

He is neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, and heartworm negative.

If you are interested in adopting Franklin, fill out an application at https://www.eunoiarescue.org/adopt.

animal.description:
Kaiya is our puppy from Critter Crusaders, she was hit by a car at just 4-5 weeks of age. You could say she has had a little bit of a "ruff" start. She is now 5 months old, thriving, and ready for her forever home. Kaiya is still a puppy so going through the puppy stages but has master potty training and is a very good girl. She is not in a kennel much so that would be a new thing for her, she is out most of the day with me, while I work from home. Let's talk about this "wiggle butt" of hers, she is SO happy to greet all the dogs and all the people. She loves other dogs, might even say a little obsessed, she wants to sleep with them, eat with them, and run around with her dogs friends. The perfect home for Kaiya would be one with another dog and a fenced in backyard. Due to her leg injury she would need lots of walks, exercise, and special attention. Kaiya's adoption fee is $300. She is spayed, microchipped, up-to-date on vaccinations and kept on preventatives. Please apply at www.adoptapal.org/adopt

animal.description:
This little girl is LULU.  She is available for adoption, but isn’t ready to go home with anyone for about 2 weeks.  She is still being treated for Demodex mange. Demodex is a mite. She isn’t contagious, but needs to get her skin healed up and then spayed before she can go to her adoptive, forever home. 

Lulu is cute, smart and very lovable and sweet. She is already learning how to sit for treats.   She is about 3 months old.  She is a white Pit Bull terrier.  She will be a big girl when she’s grown.  She’s a puppy so she loves everyone and everything that loves her and is good to her. Dogs, cats, children would all be good for Lulu if they love her right back.   

Lulu would love to have a cushy, safe indoor home filled with love and treats. No roaming around for this girl! A safe place to go potty or always on a leash with you to keep her protected - just like all dogs need.   Her fully vetted adoption fee is $95. 

Visit Lulu & the others here at the shelter 11AM - 3PM Tuesdays - Saturdays.  If you make a love connection, applications are here at the shelter.  It will not speed up the process to fill out an application ahead of time. Visits are required and all applications are reviewed with the goal of always placing our dogs in the best home for them.

*****
If don't have room in your home but do have room in your heart, you can help one of our homeless pets find a home of its own by sponsoring them. By sponsoring, you will be paying part of the adoption fee, making it possible for them to be adopted much sooner. 
            
For Adoption or Sponsorship  Information please call 270-586-3125.  
ADOPTION HOURS:  Tuesday - Saturday 11 am to 3 pm Central Time. Adoption Fee for our dogs is $95.  All dogs will be adopted fully vetted.  Spay/Neuter.  Wormed.  Heartworm tested and heartworm preventative administered.   Upon adoption, monthly preventative medications are available at a discounted rate.
animal.name: LULU

animal.description:
My name is Jazzy and I am 2 years old.  I am a friendly and affectionate girl who’s a lover a people.  I’m an energetic 45ish pounds that loves to play fetch and playing in the kiddie pool.  I love the water!  Being a curious pup at just 2 years old, there is a whole world for me to experience.  I’m looking for a family that is active and that will play with me, do fun things with me.  I am very sweet and will make a great companion.  In my foster home, I currently have a dog friend and we get along fine, but since I’m young I could use some social skills.  I can be a bit awkward trying to play with new dogs, so well balanced, well socialized dog friends might be best.  I love treats and my foster dad says I am smart and eager to please.  I love to get tummy rubs, and I often will run up to you, roll over on my back and wait to get my tummy rubbed.  I can be very silly around my humans, but that’s because I love them so much!  I am crate trained and I’m a good girl.  Some of the words my foster dad uses to describe me are cuddly, gentle, goofy, playful and very sweet.  I am hoping I get a family of my very own who will love me, play with me and give me the attention I so enjoy.  In return you will get the most sweet and cuddly companion you ever had.  If you want to know more about me or meet me in person please contact Martina Animal Rescue at martinaanimalrescue@yahoo.com.
Love, Jazzy

Due to COVID-19 precautions, all animals for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. Copy and paste the link to access the sign-up genius for an appointment: https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet for dogs and https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1 for cats.

For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to LoisLHT@gmail.com.

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE:
http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Timmy is a handsome 2 1/2 year old hound. He is 40 lbs. This sweet boy is a little timid so he will need a little extra help feeling comfortable with new people and in a new environment. 
He is mild mannered, quiet and loves other dogs. 

Timmy was brought to a rural shelter as a stray before coming to Homeward Trails. 

Adoption Coordinator: Lois
Location: Foster Home

The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program.

Weight: 64 lbs
Age: may be 8 months to 1 year
Gender: Male
Spayed/Neutered: yes
Breed: Lab mix
Color: dark brown and white

Good with adults : Yes
Good with kids: Yes but older as he is large and jumps on people
Good with other dogs: Yes he gets along with all sizes but his size and energy can intimidate.
Good with cats : Yes but enthusiastic

He still has a lot of manners to learn but right now my job is to let him have fun and get to run and play for the first time in his life!

animal.description: Bear is a very happy , active 65lb Akita Mix hunk of burning love who loves to run and play with other dogs and is great with his smaller cousins! He does want to chase cats and chickens though, so NO CATS OR CHICKENS.. He is doing wonderful with his house manners and is crate trained and housebroken. He is 1.5 years old. He can be shy with strangers ( especially men ) as we are sure he came from an abusive situation and his previous male owner dumped him down a side road. He just needs the chance to warm up and then he will be your 65lb lap dog best buddy. He is doing well with his basic obedience, food motivated. His biggest accomplishment has been learning to walk nice on a leash and not drag a human. He is very strong thus we found a no-pull easy walk harness is the perfect solution. He does wonderful in a fully fenced yard, he doesn't try to climb over or dig under. Bear loves children but may do better in a home that doesn't have toddlers because he doesn't realize he is a big dog. He is wonderful at the Vet clinic, to bathe and trim nails . Since Bear is the happiest in the colder weather, snow days are a blast, we feel that TN is not where he needs to reside forever. He does take a bit of extra bribery to get him back inside when the weather is cool. He loves to just lounge in the yard contently and is such a great outdoorsy dog. Colder weather states will be his new BEST FRIEND place to live! Bear is a big fluffy ball of fun and entertainment and is looking for his forever home.

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Would do best with a female dog or not a dominant male. No cats or chickens

animal.description:
Are you looking for a little moppy haired pooch?
Check out Chewie!!

This boy has stolen his foster moms heart and he could steal yours too in time. 

Chewie is not the most sociable pup right now but that's because he's been conditioned to stay out of the way by his former family. They couldn't give him the attention he deserves so they surrendered him to us to find him a perfect home. 
This poor guy spent the first 3 yrs of his life crated or left outside. He will often go lay in a corner or another room by himself. He frequently wants to go out, in any weather, probably because he spent so much time loose outside he's comfortable there. 

Chewie loves to be cuddled and pet, as long as your standing. It seems he wasn't allowed to cuddle on the couch and he will immediately jump down if he's taken to sit anywhere. Maybe you could teach him it's ok to cuddle on the couch!

Chewie was never fully housebroken, but has made huge strides in his foster home and rarely has accidents. He is crate trained and sleeps in his crate. He's okay on leash and working on other manners. 
As of yet, he shows no desire to play with toys or interact with the resident dogs, but that could change over time as he's young. 
He would do well being with another small dog to learn from, or he'd be ok alone with proper attention.
 
A fenced yard or area is a MUST since he has a need to be outside often and would wander the neighborhood, if given the chance. 

Are you up for the challenge to help Chewie be the best dog he can be? 
Do you have the time, patience and love to give this little guy? 
Chewie has so much potential to be a great companion in the right home. 

He's bound to be popular so get your application in soon!

Name: Chewie
Breed: Pekingese - Chihuahua mix
Sex: Male
Age: 3.5 yrs
Weight: 10 lbs
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccinations: Up to date
Heartworm: Neg.
Microchipped: Yes
Medical: Chewie has a grade 3/4 luxating patella in his right knee that may need attention as he gets older. 

BASED ON OUR OBSERVATIONS:
Good with Children: Yes
Good with Dogs: Yes
Good with Cats: Unknown

Adoption Fee: $475.00

IMPORTANT INFORMATION:
Interested in a specific dog, please fill out an application if you are interested in a dog. The number of individual inquiries is overwhelming and we are finding it difficult to respond to each one. We cannot guarantee you will receive a timely response.

Paws New England is a rescue, not a shelter, and as such we do not have our dogs housed in one location - they are in foster homes both in New England and in our southern foster homes. If you're interested in a specific dog, please complete a short online application and you will receive a reply within 48 hours so you can ask questions.

At present, if a dog is listed on our website, the dog is considered still available HOWEVER, may have applications that have come in before yours but it's still too early to know if any are a good match; therefore we encourage you to apply.

NOTICE WITH REGARD TO LOCATION OF DOGS: Please note: Paws New England is a foster-based rescue. We do not have a brick and mortar building to house the dogs we rescue. We have found that dogs in foster homes are much more adoptable because they have been observed in a home setting. Dogs listed with Paws New England typically reside in various locations throughout the south (primarily Tennessee, Texas, and Arkansas) and New England (not necessarily in the state of Rhode Island). You will be notified by the adoption coordinator of the location of the dog you are interested in so you have the ability to decide whether to pursue adoption or not.

Dogs transported to New England are done so at a fee of $150.00 paid directly to the transporting company by Paws New England; no additional transport costs are responsibility of adopter. This fee is included in the adoption donation.

Adoption donations cover pre-adoption vet costs (including vaccinations, spay/neuter when age appropriate, and heartworm testing/treatment when necessary), a microchip, and transportation to New England if necessary.

Donations for our young, healthy puppies and dogs support their fellow canines of advanced age or suffering from injuries and abuse whose donations are reduced but whose veterinary costs are typically much higher. We appreciate your understanding that your dog will help others in need.

All known information about the animal is listed above. We do our best to give accurate information, but most of our dogs are rescues and do not come with a known history.

Paws New England abides by the dog importation regulations set forth in the states of MA, CT, NH and RI.

animal.description: Copper the wonderdog is ready for you! This 17 year old sweet as pie scruffy boy has received a clean bill of health and is now looking for love just in time for Valentines day. Copper loves to shuffle around and explore his surroundings and although quite an elderly gent has been newly housetrained (who says you can't teach an old dog new tricks), and is busy learning all about the importance of the odd snuggle and cuddle too. Copper is a fairly independent fellow but he is always up for one of his favourite snacks or belly rub too. When Copper arrived into care he was a bit of a disaster medically but thanks to a lot of love and work on the part of his foster home he is now able to live his best life. In his previous home, Copper lead quite a secluded life so it took some time to build up trust and a relationship in his new home. But now- he's just one of the gang and lives happily with the other dog in his home. Copper is also cat friendly and apartment friendly too. Once in a while, due to a weak back end (which is getting better with movement and exercise), Copper will have a slight poop accident if he is super relaxed. But at 17, sometimes accidents and poop happens. It's an easy clean up and isn't often at all. After many discussions with our vet clinic, it was in Copper's best interest to not neuter him at his age. He's just looking for a quiet, hanging out lifestyle with chances to explore his surroundings at an old man pace with plenty of naps in between. Copper loves his mealtimes, is good in the car, and did we mention he loves snacks? So if you think he sounds like the quiet older gentleman who would be perfect in your home, applications to adopt are available on our website at www.happysplace.ca. Copper is being fostered near to London ON and is $450.00 to adopt.

animal.description:
My name is Nova and I am 5 years old and a 70 pound squishy bundle of love.  I am a smart and affectionate girl who is eager to please.  I am a lover of people and will pull to get close to them so I can curl up at their feet for love and affection. I am also a protector of my family.  I enjoy being pet, scratched and loved on.  If I don’t’ get enough affection, I can be pushy about letting you know I want more.  I’m a girl who knows what she wants.  I’m pretty much a puppy in a big, goofy body.  I am energetic and playful.  I love being a lap dog, but my foster mommy says I can’t be a lap dog because I am too big.  I don’t think that’s a good reason.  I think the bigger the dog the more to love!   Since I don’t seem to know my own size, I am working on boundaries.  I’m a smart girl, I love treats and am eager to learn new things.  I am looking for a family of my very own that will give me the love and attention I so desire, will play with me, and will have the patience to continue my training to make me the best girl I can be.  In return you will get a fun, playful and loyal best friend who will always be by your side.  Check out my pictures, I’m pretty cute.  If you would like to meet me in person please contact Martina Animal Rescue at: martinaanimalrescue@yahoo.com
Love, Nova

animal.description: HANK! What a perfectly wonderful houndy face! This 8 year old, 59 pound hound boy is described by his foster family as the most snuggly and sweet boy ever. Hank adores people and is the perfect blend of let’s get up and go on an outdoor adventure and let’s snuggle and snuggle even more on the sofa too. Found as a stray, Hank arrived into our care with some fur loss and a cough. With both of those well behind him now, he is a healthy fellow who is ready to live his best life with you! We can’t stress enough that although senior in age, Hank LOVES his active lifestyle. He loves walks and hikes and is happiest after he has had the chance to burn off some energy. Hank will require an adopter who is okay to help him work through a bit of his anxieties. He is overall a bit of a nervous dog until he settles into a new space and although we don’t know for sure, we imagine it is because he was not well socialized before. So what this means is a lot of things startle him. For instance- his own reflection in the mirror and loud noises. Using a calm and reassuring voice as well as time for positive experiences to grow his world has and will continue to help Hank become more and more comfortable too. Hank is a curious boy with a the nose of a hound so a fenced yard is an absolute must for him please. Sometimes Hank can be a bit mouthy when he gets really excited in his play but his mouth is always very gentle. Through an adopter who will remain committed to positive reinforcement training and relationship building with Hank, this handsome boy will continue to blossom and thrive. Known currently as a “Velcro-dog” meaning he always wants to be right by your side and as close as possible, Hank will also be looking for an adopter that doesn’t mind this part of him too. Hank has not had cat experience at all so to be safe we will be looking for a home without cats. Hank is very curious about dogs he sees on walks and was temperament tested in shelter as friendly with dogs, however does not currently live with other dogs. Due to the amount of snuggling he likes to do with his people, he may prefer to be the only dog in his home to continue to soak up all of the cuddles he can too. If you think Hank might be the perfect dog for you, you’ll find applications to adopt on our website at www.happypslace.ca where is adoption fee is $450.00 to adopt. Hank is currently being fostered in the Burlington ON area.

animal.description:
Meet Bounder, a six year old foxhound mix, who is  once again needing a new family through no fault of his own.  
Three years ago Bounder lost his mom.   This is his past story ( 3 years ago)
   My mom found out she had a very aggressive form of cancer and went for her first chemo on October 8. She came home and I kept her company until Oct 13, when she went to the Emergency Room and then to ICU. I was sure she would be back soon. Friends came and stayed nights with me at the house. Then more time passed, and days became weeks, and I just found out she is not coming home to me.
My mom was single and there is no one to take me. 
A friend found me a most awesome foster mom, who is being very patient, loving and nurturing, but she too has other animals to juggle, so I cannot stay long. I love to snuggle, am very quiet and sweet. I love to play with my favorite toy, squeaky cow ball, and sometimes I like to play a little keep away. Belly rubs and long walks are 2 favorites and I am learning to walk very well on a leash. I used to have a big fenced back yard and that would be cool to have again !  I am house broken and am used to being inside as much as I was outside. I am 80 lbs and very strong. Up to date on all my shots. I can sit and shake, but that is about the extent of my education, but I want to be the very best dog I can be, so I am going to a local training facility starting December 5, for 2 full weeks of Boarding and TRAINING !  So, whoever is lucky enough to adopt me is going to get not just a great snuggler, but a well trained pup !
Fast forward, Bounder found a wonderful home, and his training went great.  He is a great boy, who until COVID, was being walked, going with his new family places, and living a great life.   
His human family feel they cannot give Bounder the true home he needs to thrive now.  Bounder needs an active family that wants to go hiking, walking, and playing with him.  Bounder's current mom and dad are doing the best they can, but are unable to keep up with his activity level needs and want only what is best for him
Bounder loves loves loves all people, including kids, does well with other dogs and did I say he loves his spot on the couch.  He is crate trained but his crate stays open as he uses it for his safe place as so many dogs do.   He is such a good happy boy, who is ready for his family.. house trained, basic commands,  ( On my first meet with him, he sat, shaked, down, stay, and heeled walking with me)  Oh and I got kisses.
If you think Bounder is the guy for you, please fill out the on line application, link below
https://cliffordsarmyrescue.com/1423-2/

animal.description: Dallas is around a 1yr old, 56lbs and a Catahoula mix. He has the most adorable heart on his belly! This sweet boy came to the Humane Society after being picked up in Monroe. He had been wondering the streets for a long time, often spotted throughout the town until one day he was finally captured. Although shy at first, Blue quickly bubbled into a loving, bundle of joy. Blue has done great in his foster home! He is fairly potty trained but does enjoy frequent potty breaks— as he is not used to living inside. This sweet boy will do wonderfully in a home without cats or other small animals and finds it easier to play with any new brothers or sisters after getting used to them first. Blue has grown to love being inside with a warm bed and plenty of food and treats. While he will always be ready to play with his favorite ball or go on walks, his favorite pastime is snuggling up for some pets and a nap next to his caretakers. You’ll find that Blue is happiest by your side wherever you may be going. He would love to be a part of every adventure that his future family goes on. Please fill out your adoption application today at www.hsuc.org.

animal.description:
Have you ever met a dog that's, well, REALLY mischievous and you think-"hoo that dog is a LOT"-- So, take your estimation of "a LOT" and multiply that by like, 100 and you might come close to the BALL O' PERSONALITY that is Buckaroo "Buck" Rogers.  Buck may look full grown but he is alllll puppy (We estimate that he is less than a year old). He is really good about being housetrained, Is an awesome snuggler and has really gotten down the phrase "WHAT IS IN YOUR MOUTH FOR THE LOVE OF.."  Buck likes toys, people, people giving him toys, toys that are not really toys, but are actually things like hairdryers or that old pot that you had tomatoes in last year.  Buck tries VERY hard to be a good boy and most of the time he gets pretty close and even when he's not particularly succeeding, he's such a funny boy that you can't help but love him. He loves other dogs, but they like to tolerate him in smaller doses as he still thinks playing Bitey Face is hilarious. He's a Springer Spaniel, so close to 50lbs of goofiness.  Buck would REALLY appreciate a home were he can get a lot of play time and exercise! (he's good on a leash, go figure!) 

Interested in adoption? We are not currently accepting out of state (Texas) applications. Springer Spaniel Experience is a definite plus!  Adopters must have an approved application on file with us. You can find that application on our website at www.austincockerrescue.org

animal.description:
Meet Buddy Luv!
Available for Adoption
Friends of Stanly County Animals Rescue -
Locust, NC

Buddy Luv is a 1 yr old, cocker spaniel/yorkie mix who weighs 25 lbs (full grown). Mom is a cocker spaniel (who also weighs 25 lbs/Dad is the yorkie who is smaller). Whoever adopts Buddy Luv will need to have knowledge and/or experience with separation anxiety. Although it's not as bad as it once was, the issue still needs to be addressed.

He is very energetic and  needs a fenced yard so he is free to run and play as much as he wants.  The family we got him from has his best interest at heart. They were very upfront that they are not the best family/home for him. And they love him enough to reach out to us for help. So NO negatives please.

Things were good when they were working from home and were able to spend time with him. But recently, they had to return to work and that was very hard for him.  He started acting differently. Without warning, he has snapped at different family members, biting two of them. They took him to the vet to see if maybe there was something wrong. Possibly there was an issue  causing him pain, thus making him lash out. The vet found nothing.

Our rescue took him with the hope of finding him the right home with a family who knows his story and still wants to do whatever it takes to help him with whatever he needs. 

This person has to be a patient individual/family who is ready to welcome him into their family/home and give him the love and attention he deserves.

We feel like being able to have outside time and be with his owners all day will help things.. *We ask that no bashing be done towards his former owners. They truly want what is best for him, as do we.*

 Thank you!
animal.name: Buddy Luv

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Mirano is an adorable, tiny blind beagle. She is very sweet and cuddly but also vocal and curious.

Mirano is completely blind and will require a very specific kind of home. Our opthamologist says that she has no hope of recovering any sight in either eye. She will require a prescription eye drop 2-3 times a day for life. At some point, she will need her eyes surgically removed. Her adopter needs to be prepared for this surgery and its financial obligations.

Mirano is not suited to a home with young children or stairs. She enjoys other dogs and follows them around. She would do best with another dog to guide her.

animal.description:
Spongebob is a 15 year old sweetheart who is looking for a retirement home. He is a very sweet boy who was dumped on a road by his "owners" is horrible condition. Our wonderful foster, who is also a groomer, got him all fixed up and looking good again. He seems to feel a LOT better, too! 

We think Spongebob would do best in a quieter home without children, only because we believe he deserves to be the "baby" of his family for the remainder of his life. He has done well with other dogs, but calmer dogs who can give him his space would be preferred for this little guy. We think he may have some vision problems, but that isn't unusual given his age, but another reason to get him into a quieter, calmer home. 

His foster mom does use a belly band on him when he is in the house, but that is only because with old age, comes a little incontinence. It is completely normal, and shouldn't deter anyone from adopting. If you're looking for a cuddle or nap buddy, I can guarantee that Spongebob is your guy! He is said to sleep most of the time, so a nice couch, or a comfy doggie bed to crash on would be perfect!

Interested? Great! Submit an application at www.caninecastawaysrescue.org. The application approval process can take up to 7 business days. Once approved, we will contact you for that highly anticipated meet and greet with your whole family, including any existing dogs in your home!

animal.description:
Ollie is a drop-dead gorgeous 2-1/2 year old Pyr, weighing in at about 110lbs. Ollie loves people and enjoys playing with other dogs, but he would prefer to be the only dog in his home and not have to share his toys or people with another dog. He is good with dog-savvy cats, but will chase to play. He LOVES to be outside (typical Pyr), walks well on a leash, and needs a home with a fenced yard that he can hang out in during inclement weather when any sane animal would be inside. No kids under 12 for this big boy. Pyr experience is preferred.  He is currently is but can travel anywhere we do. If you want to learn more about Ollie, please complete an applicatio and then reach out to Jen.Lu@bigfluffydogs.com

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
I am fostered near FORT ATTKINSON, WI . For more information, pictures & to apply for this dog go to our website www.K9Lifeline.com If you are Reading this we ARE still TAKING Applications.
Hollywood is currently 12 pounds & will be turning 6 Months old. She has the Best sweetest, personality: Hollywood is always happy, tail wagging, handing out kisses, bouncing around with her doggy friends, running around her fenced yard & of course playing with children!!! Hollywood is perfect for a Family looking for a puppy to grow up with their younger children & another dog who likes to play. Adopting Hollywood is a 15+ Year commitment. VIDEO BELOW.
Hollywood didn't always live in the 'spot light' she spent the first 5 Months of her life being abused- as you can see in the photos the people who owned her Never got her a bigger collar, the flesh under the puppy collar grew into the collar causing what you see. Thankfully a concerned citizen convinced the owner to surrender the dog. K9LLR obtained immediate Vet care for Hollywood & now she's recovering really well. As ALWAYS K9LLR will choose the Best Matched Home for this dog.

PLEASE READ this dog's ENTIRE listing before applying.
K9 Lifeline Rescue, Inc. is licensed by the state of Wisconsin & Illinois NFP 501(c)3 Approved Rescue.
All puppies & dogs have had a wellness exam by a licensed Veterinarian, are healthy to the best of our knowledge & come with a Certified Health Certificate (CVI). All adult dogs are heartworm tested & have had spay or neuter surgery. K9LLR puppies/dogs are also up to date on vaccines, deworming & have been given Nexgard Oral or similar Flea/Tick preventative. Heartworm Preventative ( Interceptor Plus or Iverhart Max ) is given to dogs 4 months & up. All dogs are groomed prior to adoption!
The donation for this dog is $375.00. (Adult dogs are FULLY VETTED for 1 Year- ALL dogs/pups are MICROCHIPPED, come with a voucher for a FREE Wellness Exam @ Lakeview Veterinary Care) If you would like to meet/adopt this dog you Must Submit an Application which is on our website under Adoption Process. Applications are processed in the order they are received so do not delay!
All K9LLR dogs are fed a nutritious, quality 4 or 5 star dog food. As a Rescue we have had great results over the past 20 years with: CANIDAE, WELLNESS & FROMM (Made locally), brand dog & puppy food. These foods can be found at most PetCo, Feed & Whole Foods Market Stores in any state OR FREE delivery from Amazon, Bentley's PetStuff.com or Chewy. Serious inquiries only! If you are Reading this the dog IS Available & This dog is ready to go home NOW, we CANNOT HOLD any Dog or Puppy unless you would like to pre-pay a $18 per day boarding fee. Vet References ARE ALWAYS verified , if your past or present dog is not current on heartworm tests & preventative and a health exam, please do NOT apply until they are .
We reserve the right to deny any application. If you are interested in meeting this dog, please submit an application found on our Website www.K9Lifeline.com under the Adoption Process tab.
Some of our puppies are mixed breeds & in most cases we do not know who their parents were, we do our best to properly Breed ID our pups, however we cannot be 100% sure of any mix breed puppy's mix.
Please Read: Applications for this dog are handled through our Online Application ONLY in the order they are received - We keep track of which approved adopter has first choice on a particular dog using this fair system. It takes 24-72 hours to process an application. If your application is not 100% completed it will be delayed & you could loose your place in line. HAVE A QUESTION? E-Mail ApplicationK9LLR@AOL.com 2/2/21 6:59 AM

animal.description:
Collins was not treated very well during his lifetime, it is obvious from the way he acts.
He ignores the outdoor cat at his foster home, actually seems a bit timid around her.
He will bolt out of a door as soon as it is opened so he has to be watched closely until he's trained not to move when a door is opened!
He is slowly learning the leash but right now he's not happy with it at all
He must be supervised closely and on a leash while he's outside or he will run like the wind and never look back
(It did take 2 days to trap him!)
He's timid right now and a little jumpy, but he will thrive and blossom in the right home and in the right environment.
He needs someone home so that he can be around them most of the time.
He just needs to be WITH.
He's learning to come to me, just after a few hours of being here, but my loud little bossy dogs scare him.
I hate to think of what happened to this baby!
He needs a loving forever home.
He is fully vetted, neutered, microchipped, heartworm negative, on prevention, has had his bordetella, rabies, distemper parvo booster and is ready to find that forever home.

animal.description:
Clyde came with his sister Bonnie from Mexicali, Mexico. They didn't have the best start but this handsome, goofy boy is cuddly and sweet! He is a lab/shepherd mix and we expect he will be a big boy in the 50-60 pound range. Clyde is still working on his potty training, is sleeping through the night in a crate with his sister, and will need to start his leash training in his forever home. His foster mom says ""he is very sweet and loves snuggles and belly/face rubs. He is playful yet can be a bit lazy as he loves nap and snuggle time. He can be a bit goofy and I find myself laughing at some of the things he does, never fails to put a smile on my face!"" Clyde is still all puppy and has a lot to say, so he will need structure and work on his basic commands. He is a typical mouthy puppy so older kiddos or a family who can work through this phase. He loves to be outside wrestling with his sister, lounging in the grass or on plants. He would love a canine sibling and a yard to play in with humans who will introduce him to the outside world on many adventures. 

If you would like to meet Clyde please fill out an adoption application on our website and an adoption coordinator will be in contact.http://therescueddog.org/dog-adoption-application/

animal.description: Hello! I'm Dory! I'm a timid old lady that's looking for a quiet, calm home to spend my retirement. I came to these nice people at FDHS after my previous owners could no longer care for me. I did live with another dog in my previous home, but can be selective with some of the other guys here in the kennels. Loud noises and sudden movements do tend to make me nervous, so I'm looking for a slower-pace lifestyle. But don't let my passive nature fool you entirely, I can be a bit of an escape artist, so supervised outside-time would be necessary. I am very sweet with all of the humans I have met here so far and don't seem to have much of an issue with anything, other than not wanting to be alone. I am estimated to be around 8 years old, am spayed, and am up-to-date on vaccines and prevention.

animal.description:
Hi there, my name is Luna. And like my name I know you'll be over the moon for me. I am a beautiful one year old husky. Like my breed I am a very active goofy girl who will make a wonderful adventure buddy. My ideal family would have a home with a yard and give me lots of exercise. I would be happy to have another playful dog in my home but I can also live alone. I like kids and would probably do best with older or dog savvy children. I am completely potty trained, crate trained and love my dog bed. I am still working to perfect my basic commands and how to walk properly on a leash so a training class will be helpful. Lastly I love entertaining myself with tennis balls and toys.

I really am a wonderful gal. If I sound like your perfect match let's meet. I can't wait to be your buddy, go on adventures and curl up by your side.

Dogs are not placed on a first-come first-serve basis. We strive to find the perfect home for each animal, applications may take up to 48 hours to complete.

All CAWS animals are fixed, microchipped, and vaccinated. Luna's adoption fee is $200. If you are interested in adopting Luna, or another CAWS animal, please fill out an application here: http://caws.org/adoption-application. If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Zelda is the sweetest, wiggliest dog you'll ever meet! She doesn't know a stranger, and shows her excitement over meeting people by wiggling her whole body. Zelda showed up on someone's property one day and was taken in & loved by the property owner. Her world was turned upside down when one of her owners died - she spent three months acting a bit off, like she was waiting for him to come home. Life happens and the survivng owner is no longer able to care for her. She was heartbroken about leaving Zelda behind, but Zelda is such a sweet girl that we know she will be adopted quickly!
Zelda was taken to obedience classes where she learned how to sit, stay, ""wait"" for a treat on the ground, and lay down. She also does this very cute low bark when you ask her to ""say please"" for a treat! Zelda prefers the company of cats to dogs! She will happily share her bed with any feline friend willing to snuggle. She has gotten along with dogs, but she can be a bit picky, so a meet and greet with potential dog siblings is required for her. Zelda walks well on a harness, but she is a strong girl and sometimes gets focused on things out of her path. She'll need to be corrected on this behavior (she's so smart that we don't think it'll take long to figure out). She is house-trained and used to having a dog door to come in and leave as she pleases. Without a dog-door, she will sit by the ""outside"" door until she is let out. Zelda is also crate trained! She loves sleeping in the human bed, but sometimes prefers the comfort of her own crate (if you leave her crate door open, she'll spend some time in there on her own throughout the day). She does wonderful on car rides! Her favorite toys are anything that squeaks, and cat siblings that will play chase with her - she has never hurt a cat, she just likes to run with them! 
Zelda is the sweetest girl and we know she is not her happiest self here. She would be happiest in a home with someone where she can snuggle on the couch and enjoy her people being around.
DOB: 01/23/2018 Weight: 60lbs...All pets have lifetime sanctuary at Haven of the Ozarks. If they cannot remain with their adopter, they must be returned to the Haven.

animal.description:
Slate
Breed: Hound/Terrier Mix
Gender: Male
DOB: 10/23/20
Adoption Fee: $175
Slate is a bundle of puppy fun!!! This little guy will be an added plus to any home!!! His perfect home would have a fenced yard for running & playing, another dog to be his partner in crime and a boy or girl to be his best friend. Slate will benefit from puppy training, or obedience classes, this is also an excellent way to bond with your new pup. If you are interested in Slate, fill out an adoption application and make an appointment to come by and meet Slate today!!!Please read the animal bios completely before requesting additional information as we do our best to answer the most frequently ask questions in these bios. 

In order to adopt one of our animals an application must be submitted and approved. You can find these applications by going to http://humanemorgan.org/index.php?page=adoption 

ABOUT ADOPTING FROM THE HSMC: 
The shelter address is 1170 Fairground Rd. Madison, GA 30650. For more information on any of our pets, please feel free to email us at INFO@HUMANEMORGAN.ORG give us a call at 706-343-9977. 
All dogs are heartworm negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
All cats are FeLv/FIV negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
We are open 10am-5pm Monday-Saturday, we schedule our last adoption at 4pm everyday to allow our staff enough time to feed and walk dogs. 
We are an animal shelter and therefore are not able to individually potty train our residents. Many adult dogs do arrive ""house broken"" however due to animal behavior any change in environment will make an emotional impact on the animals and therefore initiate unwanted behaviors during the acclamation period. Please keep this in mind. Puppies do not have the biological maturity to maintain absolute bladder or bowel control and will require a certain degree of potty training and house breaking. Please consider the time and commitment it takes to provide the necessary building blocks for these special babies, prior to submitting your application. 
If you have any questions please email us at info@humanemorgan.org and provide name of the animal you are interested in, in the subject line. 
Thank you, HSMC Staff 

ADOPTION FEES Adoption Fees may change without notice. Always verify the fee when finalizing the adoption. 
~ Cats and Kittens ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $100 
* 1-5 Years = $75 
* Over 5 Years = $50 
** Purebred cats and kittens may be subject to special pricing 

~ Mix Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $200 
* 1 -3 Years = $175 
* 4-8 Years = $150 
* Over 8 Years = $100

~ Purebred and Designer Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $375 
* 1-3 Years = $350 
* 4-8 Years = $275 
* Over 8 Years = $150 

~ Medical and Special Needs ~ 
We have rescued dogs and cats which require additional medical care or that have special needs which are not life threatening. In these cases we may require a higher fee to help recoup the costs of their care while at our rescue.

animal.description:
Breed: Newfoundland mix
Sex: Neutered Male
DOB: ~01/25/2017
Weight: 70 lbs
Energy Level: Low 
Personality Type: Quiet, Mild-Mannered, Even-Tempered, Sweet, Gentle, People-Oriented
History: Transferred from another shelter
Good With: Dogs, Kids
Ideal Home: No apartments.
Fence Requirements: Preferred, not required.
Special Info:

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Snowball is a 6 year old, 65 lb Retriever/Spaniel mix who came to us from a rural shelter where he wasn't having any luck finding a home. He is a very shy guy who will benefit from a patient owner who is willing to give him lots of time to settle in. Snowball is familiar with living in a house, but prefers to have access to outside. He enjoys trotting around the yard, smelling the grass and the trees and watching the world go by. While it takes him a while to warm up to people, he does seem to enjoy belly rubs and will give little tail wags when he is feeling more comfortable. He is exceptionally quiet and doesn't require much; he is a homebody and doesn't really want to go for walks or be a travelling companion, he just wants to lounge at home and be there for you when you get home from a long day of work. Snowball will require a little extra time to familiarize himself with your home and learn to trust, but we think he will bond very closely to the person who can give him that and can be a successful family pet! Snowball does well with other dogs and may even benefit from a confident canine sibling to help him settle in. He would do well with older kids who are familiar with shy dogs and would greatly benefit from an enclosed yard. Snowball will also do okay with dog-savvy cats.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Meet Beautiful Omega!

Omega is a Chow mix female, aged 3 years. She has a pretty dark brown coat, blue black tongue and sparkling eyes. She is a sweetie and loves, loves, loves belly rubs! She will roll over and offer her belly to anyone! She is a good dog, but she does have a taste for chickens, so poultry siblings are not in her future. 

Omega was surrendered to us for responsible rehoming after her people fell on hard times. She is receiving wonderful care here at the shelter, but she would rather be in a nice, comfortable home! She tested negative for heart worms and is receiving monthly parasite preventatives. She is spayed, fully vaccinated and ready for immediate adoption. Please call us at 580-252-7387 or send us a message on Facebook to meet Omega.For more information, please email Stephens County Humane Society at schs@att.net, or call us at 580-252-7387 (PETS). Our animals are spayed/neutered, UTD on shots, and treated for ticks, & fleas. Cats are tested for FeLV & FIV; and dogs are tested for heart worms.

Normal adoption fee for cats is $75.00; and $100.00 for dogs, but we frequently have specials running and/or animals who have had their adoption fee sponsored, so ... call us! Let us help you find your next fur-baby!

animal.description:
Cutie Vader is 11 weeks old. He is a small smooth coated terrier mix who is initially shy but once he gets to know you he is a friendly, playful puppy. He was born on November 17th.

Vader is currently fostered with a large dog and cats. He is working on potty training and enjoys chewing ...lots of chew toys needed for this sweetie! He needs a new family with patience for a puppy and teaching him to be the best boy as he grows.

We are accepting applications now but he won't be available until after February 11th. We anticipate a large volume of applications for Vader and we apologize in advance that we will not be answering additional questions via phone or email. Please submit an application to be considered

Vader's adoption fee includes his neuter at an FLH approved veterinarian. 
**Requires signed neuter agreement**

** Please understand that we are a volunteer run organization and we do our best to respond in a timely manner. Due to the high volume of applications, emails & phone calls we receive, we may be unable to respond to everyone.
